P3para.Text:
in subsection (1), for  “the county court” substitute “
                          a residential property tribunal
                        ”;

in the sidenote, for  “court” substitute “
                          tribunal
                        ”;

Para.Text:
“



housing benefit



” means housing benefit provided by virtue of a scheme under section 123 of the Social Security Contributions and Benefits Act 1992 (c. 4);

P3para.Text:
in subsection (1), after  “the conveyance or grant may” insert “
                          (subject to section 156A(8)
                        ”;

in the sidenote, for  “reconveyance or surrender under section 157” substitute “
                          disposal under section 156A
                        ”;

in subsection (2), for  “or surrendered” substitute “
                          , conveyed, surrendered or assigned
                        ”;

Text.Addition:
if the landlord relies on the condition in sub-paragraph (3), that he has no current address for, or other means of contacting, the tenant, giving particulars of
any address (other than the premises subject to the tenancy) and other contact details (including telephone numbers or e mail addresses) which the landlord has
had for the tenant;

P3para.Text:
in paragraph (c), after  “and audit” insert “
                        or reporting
                      ”;
